age": null, "comments": [], "artist": null, "permanent": false, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/18/24104718/adobe-firefly-substance-sampler-stager-3d-tools-beta", "language": "en", "album": "", "bookmarked": false, "tags": [], "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_votes": 0, "vote": 0, "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-03-18T13:54:19+00:00", "title": "Adobe Substance 3D\u2019s AI features can turn text into backgrounds and textures"}, {"thumbnail": null, "page_rating": 94, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Sony PlayStation VR 2 headset and handheld controllers being worn by a model.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/YGs-PY9PGHe8T7Pm8RVs60DdfZc=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73214685/236532_PSVR2_AKrales_0279.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Sony\u2019s PlayStation VR2.</em> | Photo by Amelia Holowaty Krales / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"aQvhgL\">After producing in excess of two million units of its latest virtual reality headset, <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-03-18/sony-hits-pause-on-psvr2-production-as-unsold-inventory-piles-up\"><em>Bloomberg</em> is reporting</a> that Sony is hitting pause on production to try and shift its unsold inventory. The <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23601368/sony-playstation-ps-vr2-review-virtual-reality\">PlayStation VR2</a> launched last February for $549 as an accessory for the PlayStation 5, but IDC data suggests that shipments have decli", "user": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_contents": 94, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "age": null, "comments": [], "artist": null, "permanent": false, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/18/24104649/sony-pausing-playstation-vr2-production", "language": "en", "album": "", "bookmarked": false, "tags": [], "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_votes": 0, "vote": 0, "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-03-18T11:06:40+00:00", "title": "Sony is reportedly pausing PSVR2 production to clear excess inventory"}, {"thumbnail": null, "page_rating": 94, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The iPhone 15 Pro (blue titanium) and 15 Pro Max (white titanium) standing next to one another.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/BI2SZhoGA6JTedrMH5qo95NYUa4=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73214559/236794_iPhone_15_pro_pro_Max_VPavic_0019.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Last year\u2019s iPhone 15 Pro and Pro Max.</em> | Photo by Vjeran Pavic / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"cNqd0K\">Apple is reportedly in \u201cactive negotiations\u201d with Google to bring its Gemini generative AI technology to the iPhone, <a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-03-18/apple-in-talks-to-license-google-gemini-for-iphone-ios-18-generative-ai-tools\"><em>Bloomberg </em>reports</a>, and has also considered using OpenAI\u2019s ChatGPT.</p>\n<p id=\"pyosae\">CEO Tim Cook has <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/1/24058647/apple-ceo-tim-cook-teases-generative-ai-iphone\">already confirmed</a> that Apple is spending \u201ca tremend", "user": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_contents": 94, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "age": null, "comments": [], "artist": null, "permanent": false, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/18/24104626/apple-license-google-gemini-generative-ai-openai-chatgpt", "language": "en", "album": "", "bookmarked": false, "tags": [], "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_votes": 0, "vote": 0, "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-03-18T09:30:34+00:00", "title": "Apple\u2019s AI ambitions could include Google or OpenAI"}, {"thumbnail": null, "page_rating": 94, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Rendering of Snapdragon 8S Gen 3 chipset.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/swKNNhDZSxlr8JElDzSATjYRQZM=/8x0:1993x1323/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73214505/Snapdragon_8s_Gen_3___Key_Visual.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Is it upper midrange? Is it lesser high-end? Hard to say.</em> | Image: Qualcomm</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"9dm9Ra\">Qualcomm just launched a new chipset that\u2019s designed to sit just below its current flagship in terms of capabilities and price. The Snapdragon 8S Gen 3 aims to bring most of the 8 Gen 3\u2019s features \u2014 including support for on-device generative AI models \u2014 to more affordable phones. It represents a new tier for the top-of-the-line 8-series chips, and it\u2019s also a little bit confusing.</p>\n<p id=\"AlKle6\">Before we get into all that, let\u2019s start with the straightforward stuff: the 8S Gen 3 includes a GPU similar to the standard 8 Gen 3, though it has one less performance core and runs at", "user": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_contents": 94, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "age": null, "comments": [], "artist": null, "permanent": false, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/18/24101903/qualcomm-snapdragon-8s-gen-3-chipset-on-device-ai", "language": "en", "album": "", "bookmarked": false, "tags": [], "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_votes": 0, "vote": 0, "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-03-18T06:30:00+00:00", "title": "Qualcomm\u2019s new 8S Gen 3 targets not-quite flagship phones"}, {"thumbnail": null, "page_rating": 94, "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration of the Grok logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/dKqEpno29iZc9Trd-p47BQOQ8Us=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73214220/STK262_GROK_B.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"bHoRBC\">On March 11th, Elon Musk <a href=\"https://twitter.com/elonmusk/status/1767108624038449405\">said</a> xAI would open source its <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24080217/elon-musk-xai-fundraising-grok-ai\">AI chatbot Grok</a>, and now an open release <a href=\"https://github.com/xai-org/grok-1\">is available on GitHub</a>. This will allow researchers and developers to build on the model and impact how xAI updates Grok in the future as it competes with rival tech from OpenAI, Meta, Google, and others.</p>\n<p id=\"J3Hbbv\"><a href=\"https://x.ai/blog/grok-os\">A company blog post</a> explains that this open release includes the \u201cbase model weights and network architecture\u201d of the \u201c314 bi", "user": null, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_contents": 94, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "age": null, "comments": [], "artist": null, "permanent": false, "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/17/24097810/xai-open-source-grok-musk-generative-ai-llm", "language": "en", "album": "", "bookmarked": false, "tags": [], "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_votes": 0, "vote": 0, "dead": false, "date_published": "2024-03-18T01:10:46+00:00", "title": "xAI open sources Grok"}]